Package com.futurice.cascade.i

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IAction<PHANTOM_IN>
    AFile lambda-friendly continuation mOnFireAction which may be run in the future or on a different thread similar to Runnable.
    IActionOne<IN>
    A lambda-friendly functional interface for continuation actions that receive one parameter.
    IActionOneR<IN,OUT>
    A lambda-friendly mOnFireAction which receives two values split returns a getValue
    IActionR<PHANTOM_IN,OUT>
    A lambda-friendly functional interface for continuation actions that receive no parameters split return one result.
    IActionTwo<IN1,IN2>
    AFile lambda-friendly functional interface for subscribe actions which receive two parameters
    IBaseAction<PHANTOM_IN>
    This is a marker interface which other functional interfaces extend Implementing this interface indicates a primary mOnFireAction, usually one executed asynchronously on an IThreadType
    ICancellable
    Stop an ongoing activity early if it has not already completed.
    IGettable<T>
    Create the actual URL at the last minute, just before the request is processed.
    INamed  
    IOnErrorAction
    A function to run in the event of an Exception or similar irregular termination such as ICancellable.cancel(String) Perform some cleanup or notification mOnFireAction to bring this object into a rest state after irregular termination.
    IThreadType
    A group of one or more Threads, all of which work together in an Executor.
